definitions.definition: To elicit, evoke, or emphasize a particular quality.
definitions.example: She brings out the best in him.

definitions.definition: To place (something new for public sale) on the market; roll out.
definitions.example: Acme sweets have just brought out a tasty new chocolate bar.

definitions.definition: To make a shy person more confident.
definitions.example: His new job has noticeably brought him out.

definitions.definition: To cause a visible symptom such as spots or a rash
definitions.example: Eating strawberries always brings me out in a rash.

definitions.definition: To introduce (a young woman) formally into society.
